Aug. 1541) of Chur3 who since c. 1515 had been studying medicine at Basle, and who is described in Glareanus’ Eleyiae, 14 Nov. 1516. as ‘medicus et musicus '- In 1520 he had a school at Basle of twenty pupils who lived with him (cf. BRE. 157). In 1528 he was at Besanqon (EE. 883, perhaps practising as a physician. By 1538 he had re- turned to Basle‚ and was Rector of the University May—Oct.; the first student matriculated by him being his own son, of the same name.
